title: Chet Baker - Baby Breeze (Verve,1965) @320kbps
description:
MP3/320kbps

On this mid-Sixties session Chet Baker performed masterfully on the flugelhorn in a place of a recently stolen trumpet, adding yet another texture to his arsenal of lyrical and subdued sounds.
Featured on this release are Baker&#039;s vocals on six tracks as well as pianist Bob James and guitarist Kenny Burrell. Five bonus tracks, including two which are previously unissued, have been added to the original-LP&#039;s selections.

Personnel:
Chet Baker - vocals, flugelhorn
Bobby Scott, Bob James - piano
Kenny Burrell - guitar
Frank Strozier - alto saxophone, flute
Phil Urso - tenor saxophone
Michael Fleming - bass
Charlie Rice - drums

Recorded November 1964, New York City: tracks 1-3, 5-7, and 9-12 on November 14 at A & R Studios; track 4, 8, and 13-15 on November 20
